Agreement
 is the most important aspect of Hebrew adjectives.

Adjectives will agree with the nouns they modify in gender and number.

There are three different types of Hebrew adjectives
(Click/tap on each category)
-requires a helping verb such as is or are in English translation.

-substitute or stand in the place of the noun.
-usually appears with the article
-agree in gender and number with the object in whose place it stands.

Adjectives
Hebrew Adjectives function much like their English counterparts.  
An adjective tells us something about an object or person.

Unlike English adjectives, Hebrew adjectives inflect for gender and number.
